[
    {
        "text": "on september 1st 1859 a gigantic",
        "start": 0.719,
        "duration": 4.161
    },
    {
        "text": "explosion on the sun",
        "start": 3.76,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "sent radiation and matter flying towards",
        "start": 4.88,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "earth resulting in one of the largest",
        "start": 7.04,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "geomagnetic storms on record",
        "start": 9.2,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "the auroras that night were bright",
        "start": 11.36,
        "duration": 3.279
    },
    {
        "text": "enough to read by and were visible as",
        "start": 12.799,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "far south as hawaii but the real impact",
        "start": 14.639,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "came from the disruption of the",
        "start": 17.039,
        "duration": 2.641
    },
    {
        "text": "telegraph system",
        "start": 18.32,
        "duration": 3.119
    },
    {
        "text": "across europe and north america",
        "start": 19.68,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "telegraph systems failed",
        "start": 21.439,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "in some cases shocking their operators",
        "start": 23.199,
        "duration": 5.521
    },
    {
        "text": "or throwing sparks from their machinery",
        "start": 25.279,
        "duration": 6.0
    },
    {
        "text": "what in the world or should i say",
        "start": 28.72,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "universe",
        "start": 31.279,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "caused this crazy storm and should we be",
        "start": 32.239,
        "duration": 4.761
    },
    {
        "text": "worried about it happening again",
        "start": 35.04,
        "duration": 5.179
    },
    {
        "text": "[Music]",
        "start": 37.0,
        "duration": 3.219
    },
    {
        "text": "so we know the sun produces energy as",
        "start": 40.96,
        "duration": 3.439
    },
    {
        "text": "light and heat",
        "start": 43.12,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "but we don't often think about all of",
        "start": 44.399,
        "duration": 3.121
    },
    {
        "text": "the wild things happening",
        "start": 45.92,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "on and below its surface and some of",
        "start": 47.52,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "those things can affect us",
        "start": 49.76,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "all the way down here on earth our sun",
        "start": 51.12,
        "duration": 5.279
    },
    {
        "text": "is a yellow dwarf star",
        "start": 54.64,
        "duration": 4.719
    },
    {
        "text": "so large that the volume of 1.3 million",
        "start": 56.399,
        "duration": 5.041
    },
    {
        "text": "earths could fit inside of it",
        "start": 59.359,
        "duration": 4.641
    },
    {
        "text": "but if we travel deep inside our sun the",
        "start": 61.44,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "temperature is 15 million degrees",
        "start": 64.0,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "celsius",
        "start": 66.08,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "which is hot and dense enough to fuse",
        "start": 66.88,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": "hydrogen atoms into helium",
        "start": 68.96,
        "duration": 3.839
    },
    {
        "text": "a process called nuclear fusion that",
        "start": 70.799,
        "duration": 5.281
    },
    {
        "text": "gives off massive amounts of energy",
        "start": 72.799,
        "duration": 5.041
    },
    {
        "text": "but today we're more interested in",
        "start": 76.08,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "what's happening on the relatively",
        "start": 77.84,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "cooler surface of the sun called the",
        "start": 80.08,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "photosphere",
        "start": 82.56,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "let's back up a little bit a little more",
        "start": 84.0,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "just a touch farther",
        "start": 86.32,
        "duration": 3.88
    },
    {
        "text": "that's better the surface of the sun is",
        "start": 87.84,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "5500 degrees celsius",
        "start": 90.2,
        "duration": 4.2
    },
    {
        "text": "and covered in gases that are constantly",
        "start": 92.24,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "moving and changing",
        "start": 94.4,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "it's covered by a thin layer called the",
        "start": 95.759,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "chromosphere this layer is usually hard",
        "start": 97.52,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "to",
        "start": 99.759,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "see but can be seen as bright red when",
        "start": 100.0,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "viewed with specific light filters or",
        "start": 102.079,
        "duration": 3.201
    },
    {
        "text": "during a solar eclipse",
        "start": 103.84,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "right above that is the corona the super",
        "start": 105.28,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "hot outer atmosphere of plasma that",
        "start": 107.36,
        "duration": 3.119
    },
    {
        "text": "looks like a crown or",
        "start": 109.04,
        "duration": 4.079
    },
    {
        "text": "corona during a solar eclipse the corona",
        "start": 110.479,
        "duration": 4.881
    },
    {
        "text": "extends far above the surface of the sun",
        "start": 113.119,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "eventually merging into the solar wind",
        "start": 115.36,
        "duration": 3.8
    },
    {
        "text": "that moves throughout the solar system",
        "start": 117.119,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "[Music]",
        "start": 119.16,
        "duration": 3.8
    },
    {
        "text": "these images from nasa's solar dynamics",
        "start": 120.64,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "observatory were taken with special",
        "start": 122.96,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "telescopes that allow us to look at the",
        "start": 124.56,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "solar atmosphere",
        "start": 126.32,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "in many different wavelengths of light",
        "start": 127.36,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "each telling us something a little",
        "start": 129.44,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "different about what's happening",
        "start": 130.879,
        "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
        "text": "and if you look at these many different",
        "start": 133.04,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "images you'll see that there are giant",
        "start": 134.48,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "explosions",
        "start": 136.64,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "big spots and huge loops of plasma",
        "start": 137.68,
        "duration": 6.16
    },
    {
        "text": "all over the sun's surface",
        "start": 140.72,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "so what is up with the sun it's doing",
        "start": 143.92,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "some",
        "start": 146.879,
        "duration": 3.841
    },
    {
        "text": "wild and seemingly mysterious things",
        "start": 147.28,
        "duration": 5.76
    },
    {
        "text": "well hot electrically charged plasma",
        "start": 150.72,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "flows within the sun",
        "start": 153.04,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "constantly moving the movement of these",
        "start": 154.16,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "charged particles",
        "start": 156.72,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "creates currents and these electrical",
        "start": 157.68,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "currents create magnetic fields",
        "start": 159.44,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "this phenomena of turning motion into",
        "start": 161.36,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "magnetism is called a dynamo",
        "start": 163.04,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "and so the sun's magnetic field is a",
        "start": 165.04,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "result of the solar dynamo",
        "start": 166.56,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "compared to earth's relatively tame",
        "start": 169.04,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "magnetic field with just a north and",
        "start": 170.64,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "south pole",
        "start": 172.4,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "these looping twisting fields of",
        "start": 173.44,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "magnetism on the sun are far more",
        "start": 175.2,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "dynamic",
        "start": 177.12,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "in this image of the sun you can see",
        "start": 178.56,
        "duration": 3.679
    },
    {
        "text": "lots of looping lines that seem to come",
        "start": 180.4,
        "duration": 3.199
    },
    {
        "text": "off of its surface",
        "start": 182.239,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "these are prominences giant loops of",
        "start": 183.599,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "plasma that stretch out from the sun's",
        "start": 186.319,
        "duration": 2.881
    },
    {
        "text": "photosphere",
        "start": 188.0,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "the plasma is composed of electrically",
        "start": 189.2,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "charged hydrogen and helium",
        "start": 191.04,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": "these prominences follow the sun's",
        "start": 193.36,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "magnetic field lines and extend out into",
        "start": 194.959,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "the corona the sun's extended atmosphere",
        "start": 197.04,
        "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
        "text": "scientists are still trying to figure",
        "start": 200.239,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "out exactly how and why",
        "start": 201.84,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "they happen oh and these prominences are",
        "start": 203.76,
        "duration": 5.839
    },
    {
        "text": "huge just look at this image of earth",
        "start": 207.12,
        "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
        "text": "superimposed for scale",
        "start": 209.599,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "but prominences are just the start of",
        "start": 212.08,
        "duration": 4.799
    },
    {
        "text": "weird things happening on the sun",
        "start": 214.319,
        "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
        "text": "see these dark spots they're called",
        "start": 216.879,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "sunspots and what's happening inside of",
        "start": 218.799,
        "duration": 2.401
    },
    {
        "text": "them is",
        "start": 220.56,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "really crazy these are areas where the",
        "start": 221.2,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "magnetic field of the sun has become",
        "start": 223.44,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "so great that it causes the atmospheric",
        "start": 225.28,
        "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
        "text": "pressure in the area to decrease",
        "start": 227.68,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "what happens is the intense magnetic",
        "start": 229.76,
        "duration": 3.679
    },
    {
        "text": "field prevents hot gas from the center",
        "start": 231.68,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "of the sun from flowing outward towards",
        "start": 233.439,
        "duration": 2.641
    },
    {
        "text": "the surface",
        "start": 235.12,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "creating a cool spot on the sun that",
        "start": 236.08,
        "duration": 3.439
    },
    {
        "text": "appears darker than the surrounding",
        "start": 237.92,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "areas",
        "start": 239.519,
        "duration": 4.161
    },
    {
        "text": "sometimes astronomers will observe rapid",
        "start": 241.36,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "intense changes in brightness on the",
        "start": 243.68,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "surface of the sun",
        "start": 245.28,
        "duration": 4.319
    },
    {
        "text": "like this these are solar flares",
        "start": 246.48,
        "duration": 5.2
    },
    {
        "text": "solar flares are intense bursts of",
        "start": 249.599,
        "duration": 4.081
    },
    {
        "text": "radiation from the sun that occur when",
        "start": 251.68,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "huge amounts of stored magnetic energy",
        "start": 253.68,
        "duration": 5.04
    },
    {
        "text": "are rapidly released solar flares create",
        "start": 255.84,
        "duration": 4.799
    },
    {
        "text": "intense bursts of light that can last",
        "start": 258.72,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "for minutes or for hours",
        "start": 260.639,
        "duration": 4.881
    },
    {
        "text": "and often occur near sunspots sometimes",
        "start": 262.32,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "when this magnetic energy is released",
        "start": 265.52,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "eruptions on the surface of the sun can",
        "start": 267.6,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "also send billions of tons of solar",
        "start": 269.36,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "matter",
        "start": 271.6,
        "duration": 2.879
    },
    {
        "text": "flying out into space this is called a",
        "start": 272.0,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "coronal mass ejection or",
        "start": 274.479,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "cme these send giant clouds of",
        "start": 276.08,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "magnetized particles",
        "start": 278.88,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "hurtling out into space flares and cmes",
        "start": 280.16,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "often happen together",
        "start": 283.28,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "with a bright flash followed by the",
        "start": 284.56,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "giant arcing explosion",
        "start": 286.24,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "but cmes can also happen on their own",
        "start": 288.08,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "and these can be",
        "start": 290.96,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "big explosions cmes can contain a",
        "start": 292.08,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "billion tons of matter and can travel",
        "start": 294.96,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "faster than 5 million miles per hour",
        "start": 296.72,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "they can accelerate protons and",
        "start": 298.88,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "electrons ahead of them as they travel",
        "start": 300.24,
        "duration": 2.399
    },
    {
        "text": "towards us",
        "start": 301.84,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "creating storms of these fast-moving",
        "start": 302.639,
        "duration": 4.641
    },
    {
        "text": "high-energy particles",
        "start": 304.72,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "and despite the sun being 93 million",
        "start": 307.28,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": "miles away",
        "start": 310.08,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "all of these solar weather events can",
        "start": 311.199,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "still have effects right here on earth",
        "start": 312.72,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "from stunningly beautiful auroras to",
        "start": 314.96,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "radio blackouts",
        "start": 317.6,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "light x-rays and gamma rays from a flyer",
        "start": 319.36,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "arrive at the earth in just 8 minutes",
        "start": 321.84,
        "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
        "text": "but cmes can take hours to days to",
        "start": 324.0,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "arrive",
        "start": 326.8,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "bombarding the earth with charged",
        "start": 327.52,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "particles and magnetic field from the",
        "start": 329.12,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "corona",
        "start": 330.8,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "thankfully our atmosphere and",
        "start": 332.32,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "magnetosphere protect our fragile human",
        "start": 334.16,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "bodies",
        "start": 336.32,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "from most of this fast-moving particles",
        "start": 336.88,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "from the sun",
        "start": 339.28,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "interact with the earth's magnetic field",
        "start": 340.08,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "and particles trapped in our local space",
        "start": 341.68,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "environment",
        "start": 343.44,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "eventually the energy transfer results",
        "start": 344.32,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "in charged particles colliding with",
        "start": 346.32,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "oxygen and nitrogen in our uppermost",
        "start": 348.08,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "atmosphere",
        "start": 350.16,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "causing auroras like the northern lights",
        "start": 350.96,
        "duration": 4.959
    },
    {
        "text": "and the emitted light is specific to",
        "start": 354.32,
        "duration": 4.159
    },
    {
        "text": "each molecule oxygen atoms typically",
        "start": 355.919,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "give off a greenish yellow or red light",
        "start": 358.479,
        "duration": 5.521
    },
    {
        "text": "nitrogen atoms give auroras a blue hue",
        "start": 361.199,
        "duration": 5.041
    },
    {
        "text": "and nitrogen gas can appear a reddish",
        "start": 364.0,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "pink",
        "start": 366.24,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "usually you can only see auroras towards",
        "start": 368.08,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "earth's poles",
        "start": 370.0,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "this is because earth's own magnetic",
        "start": 371.12,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "field lines direct the stream of",
        "start": 372.56,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "incoming particles towards the poles",
        "start": 374.08,
        "duration": 4.559
    },
    {
        "text": "but sometimes a solar event is so big",
        "start": 376.319,
        "duration": 5.841
    },
    {
        "text": "you can see it across the world",
        "start": 378.639,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "and that's what happened in 1859 richard",
        "start": 382.319,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "carrington an amateur astronomer",
        "start": 385.199,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "was peering through his telescope and",
        "start": 387.039,
        "duration": 3.361
    },
    {
        "text": "sketching out sunspots",
        "start": 388.88,
        "duration": 4.159
    },
    {
        "text": "when he noticed two bright white patches",
        "start": 390.4,
        "duration": 5.04
    },
    {
        "text": "erupting from the spots",
        "start": 393.039,
        "duration": 4.081
    },
    {
        "text": "these two flares disappeared in about",
        "start": 395.44,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "five minutes but caused the biggest",
        "start": 397.12,
        "duration": 5.6
    },
    {
        "text": "recorded geomagnetic storm",
        "start": 399.199,
        "duration": 5.921
    },
    {
        "text": "early the next morning just before dawn",
        "start": 402.72,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "stunningly bright auroras appeared",
        "start": 405.12,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "across the world",
        "start": 406.96,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "visible as far south as cuba the bahamas",
        "start": 408.16,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "and hawaii",
        "start": 410.479,
        "duration": 2.801
    },
    {
        "text": "people in the northeastern u.s reported",
        "start": 411.36,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "being able to read the newspaper by the",
        "start": 413.28,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "light of the auroras alone",
        "start": 414.88,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "and a baltimore newspaper described the",
        "start": 416.72,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "city being lit up as if under a luminous",
        "start": 418.56,
        "duration": 4.079
    },
    {
        "text": "cloud",
        "start": 420.88,
        "duration": 4.159
    },
    {
        "text": "but as beautiful as they were they also",
        "start": 422.639,
        "duration": 4.801
    },
    {
        "text": "caused huge disruptions to the telegraph",
        "start": 425.039,
        "duration": 3.361
    },
    {
        "text": "system",
        "start": 427.44,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "and yes as you're watching this on",
        "start": 428.4,
        "duration": 4.239
    },
    {
        "text": "youtube that might sound kinda quaint",
        "start": 430.24,
        "duration": 4.6
    },
    {
        "text": "but at the time it was a major method of",
        "start": 432.639,
        "duration": 4.641
    },
    {
        "text": "communication",
        "start": 434.84,
        "duration": 4.52
    },
    {
        "text": "in its simplest form a telegraph is a",
        "start": 437.28,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "transmitter and a receiver",
        "start": 439.36,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "connected by an open circuit we talked",
        "start": 440.8,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "more about circuits in our episode about",
        "start": 442.88,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "the world's biggest batteries",
        "start": 444.4,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "you can send a telegraph message by",
        "start": 446.4,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "pressing down on a transmission key",
        "start": 448.16,
        "duration": 4.159
    },
    {
        "text": "which completes the circuit this sends",
        "start": 450.0,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "an electric pulse to the receiver",
        "start": 452.319,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "which causes an electromagnet in the",
        "start": 454.16,
        "duration": 4.319
    },
    {
        "text": "receiver to attract a small iron arm",
        "start": 456.0,
        "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
        "text": "whose movement makes a mark on a paper",
        "start": 458.479,
        "duration": 4.241
    },
    {
        "text": "by tapping away in morse code you can",
        "start": 460.96,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "send messages over long distances using",
        "start": 462.72,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "electricity",
        "start": 464.72,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "so yeah gigantic bursts of",
        "start": 466.479,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "electromagnetic radiation from the sun",
        "start": 468.4,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "can kind of mess with a system based on",
        "start": 470.24,
        "duration": 4.17
    },
    {
        "text": "sending precise electric signals",
        "start": 472.08,
        "duration": 3.679
    },
    {
        "text": "[Music]",
        "start": 474.41,
        "duration": 3.509
    },
    {
        "text": "when a cme reaches our planet the",
        "start": 475.759,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "gigantic blob",
        "start": 477.919,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "of solar atmosphere and magnetic field",
        "start": 479.199,
        "duration": 4.321
    },
    {
        "text": "rattles the earth like a bell",
        "start": 481.68,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "generating electric currents both in our",
        "start": 483.52,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "atmosphere and",
        "start": 485.52,
        "duration": 3.119
    },
    {
        "text": "in long conductors like pipes and power",
        "start": 486.72,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": "lines this is what created",
        "start": 488.639,
        "duration": 4.161
    },
    {
        "text": "the massive electrical currents that",
        "start": 490.639,
        "duration": 4.161
    },
    {
        "text": "overwhelmed the telegraph system",
        "start": 492.8,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "causing some to shoot out sparks and",
        "start": 494.8,
        "duration": 3.679
    },
    {
        "text": "even lighting the telegraph paper on",
        "start": 496.8,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "fire in places",
        "start": 498.479,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "many lines stopped working but some",
        "start": 500.24,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "telegraph operators reported that the",
        "start": 502.16,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "aurora induced currents allowed them to",
        "start": 503.84,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "transmit messages",
        "start": 505.68,
        "duration": 2.799
    },
    {
        "text": "even after they had unplugged the",
        "start": 506.8,
        "duration": 4.399
    },
    {
        "text": "batteries from their machines",
        "start": 508.479,
        "duration": 4.721
    },
    {
        "text": "but first-hand accounts aren't the only",
        "start": 511.199,
        "duration": 3.361
    },
    {
        "text": "way to investigate past",
        "start": 513.2,
        "duration": 4.639
    },
    {
        "text": "geomagnetic storms sometimes we can see",
        "start": 514.56,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "the side effects of giant solar storms",
        "start": 517.839,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "trapped in ice",
        "start": 519.68,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "cmes act like giant bulldozers plowing",
        "start": 521.279,
        "duration": 4.161
    },
    {
        "text": "through interplanetary space",
        "start": 523.68,
        "duration": 3.279
    },
    {
        "text": "pushing big waves of high-energy",
        "start": 525.44,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "particles including protons and",
        "start": 526.959,
        "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
        "text": "electrons ahead of them",
        "start": 528.72,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "when these particles collide with the",
        "start": 530.56,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "atoms and molecules in our atmosphere",
        "start": 532.0,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "they create radioactive atoms some like",
        "start": 534.08,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "carbon 14",
        "start": 537.12,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "are incorporated into living organisms",
        "start": 538.24,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "and let us do things like carbon dating",
        "start": 540.16,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "and if you want to watch more about the",
        "start": 542.56,
        "duration": 3.279
    },
    {
        "text": "chemistry that enables carbon dating",
        "start": 544.0,
        "duration": 5.279
    },
    {
        "text": "check out our episode on lake nios",
        "start": 545.839,
        "duration": 6.0
    },
    {
        "text": "but beyond just carbon 14 these storms",
        "start": 549.279,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "of particles can create radioactive",
        "start": 551.839,
        "duration": 4.241
    },
    {
        "text": "isotopes like beryllium 10 and chlorine",
        "start": 553.68,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "36",
        "start": 556.08,
        "duration": 2.319
    },
    {
        "text": "which can then fall down to earth and",
        "start": 556.88,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "become locked in ice",
        "start": 558.399,
        "duration": 4.481
    },
    {
        "text": "by drilling cores into the ice in",
        "start": 561.2,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "undisturbed areas like antarctica and",
        "start": 562.88,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "greenland",
        "start": 564.88,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "scientists can find evidence of these",
        "start": 565.68,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "particle storms associated with cmes",
        "start": 567.12,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "that happened",
        "start": 569.279,
        "duration": 2.401
    },
    {
        "text": "long before we were able to track them",
        "start": 570.0,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "with modern technology",
        "start": 571.68,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "in fact ice cores have shown evidence of",
        "start": 573.36,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "three major solar storms in 994 ce",
        "start": 575.2,
        "duration": 7.12
    },
    {
        "text": "775 ce and 660 bce",
        "start": 578.72,
        "duration": 5.44
    },
    {
        "text": "all three were also corroborated by",
        "start": 582.32,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "spikes in radioactive carbon found in",
        "start": 584.16,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "tree rings",
        "start": 586.08,
        "duration": 3.199
    },
    {
        "text": "while early evidence showed that there",
        "start": 587.68,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "may also be a trace of the 1859 event in",
        "start": 589.279,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "an ice core",
        "start": 591.76,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "it's more likely that what the",
        "start": 592.8,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "scientists saw was in fact due to large",
        "start": 594.32,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "amounts of burning biomass",
        "start": 596.399,
        "duration": 4.641
    },
    {
        "text": "like large forest fires in north america",
        "start": 598.08,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "which could mean",
        "start": 601.04,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "that these other three events were much",
        "start": 602.16,
        "duration": 5.52
    },
    {
        "text": "much bigger than the 1859 event",
        "start": 604.48,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "so should we be worried about another",
        "start": 607.68,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "event like this happening and",
        "start": 609.76,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "wiping out all of our technology we've",
        "start": 611.2,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "progressed quite a bit since the",
        "start": 613.68,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "telegraph",
        "start": 615.2,
        "duration": 2.319
    },
    {
        "text": "but that really just makes us more at",
        "start": 615.92,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "risk if something of this skill were to",
        "start": 617.519,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "happen today",
        "start": 619.04,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": "your phone the internet gps radios",
        "start": 620.079,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "credit cards the transformers that help",
        "start": 622.959,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "supply power to your home",
        "start": 624.48,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "all of these could be affected by a big",
        "start": 626.079,
        "duration": 3.521
    },
    {
        "text": "enough geomagnetic storm",
        "start": 627.76,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "and the biggest fear is that these solar",
        "start": 629.6,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "storms could affect the power grid",
        "start": 631.2,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "which would affect anything that relies",
        "start": 632.72,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "on electricity",
        "start": 634.48,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "so basically everything",
        "start": 635.92,
        "duration": 5.599
    },
    {
        "text": "and we've had a relatively recent taste",
        "start": 639.6,
        "duration": 3.359
    },
    {
        "text": "of what this could do to our modern",
        "start": 641.519,
        "duration": 2.401
    },
    {
        "text": "systems",
        "start": 642.959,
        "duration": 3.041
    },
    {
        "text": "in the 70s a cme knocked out long",
